08/07/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Prosecutors announced on Saturday (July 7th) that charges have been filed against eight people -- described only as active and reserve members of the former Yugoslav People's Army -- for crimes against Croat civilians and prisoners of war in the Morinje detention centre between October1991 and July 1992.
In other news, US Assistant Secretary of State Daniel Fried arrived in Montenegro on Sunday.
He is the most senior State Department representative to visit since the republic announced its independence last year.
On Monday, chief UN war crimes prosecutor Carla del Ponte is expected to visit Montenegro for talks with senior officials, before heading on to Bosnia and Herzegovina and Croatia.
(Antena M, Vjesti, Makfax - 08/07/07;
RTCG - 07/07/07)
